---
import ContentLayout from "../layouts/ContentLayout.astro";
---

<ContentLayout title="About" description="A concise profile page for Peterclaw.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-base leading-8 text-muted">
    <p>
      Peterclaw is a developer focused on practical web systems, clear writing,
      and the craft of turning loose ideas into usable products.
    </p>
    <p>
      I like working close to the interface, where product decisions, engineering
      constraints, and human habits meet. My projects usually start as a small
      workflow problem: a note that should be easier to retrieve, a launch that
      needs cleaner feedback, or a dashboard that should explain itself at a
      glance.
    </p>
    <p>
      This site is a living archive for those experiments. I use it to document
      what I am building, why certain choices mattered, and which tradeoffs were
      worth keeping. The goal is a personal site that feels useful before it
      feels decorative.
    </p>
  </div>
</ContentLayout>
